NOTE: This is a placeholder showing the copyright notice and the standard
Apache 2.0 boilerplate that should appear at the top of source files. The
full license text is approximately 12 KB and is not duplicated here.

To populate this file with the full Apache 2.0 license text, run one of:

    curl -L https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.txt -o LICENSE

    # or, when initializing a new GitHub repo with `gh`:
    gh repo create korlogos/fatfinger6000 --license Apache-2.0 ...

GitHub will also offer to add the full LICENSE text automatically if you
select "Apache License 2.0" when creating the repository through the web UI.

The full Apache 2.0 license text is unchanged worldwide; fetching from
apache.org or GitHub's license templates produces the canonical version.
